article.headline: Dayton 62, Cornell 51
article.story: DAYTON, Ohio (AP) -- Freshman Norman Plummer came off the bench to score 12 points, and Dayton never trailed in its 62-51 victory over Cornell on Sunday night. Trent Meacham, also a freshman, scored 11 points off the bench for the Flyers (7-5). Monty Scott added 10 points, all in the second half, and also grabbed a career-high 12 rebounds. Lenny Collins was 8-for-8 from the free-throw line and finished with 13 points for Cornell (5-8). Eric Taylor added 10 points. Dayton opened the game on a 13-4 run, and led 25-18 at the half. The Big Red trailed 62-40 with 3:50 to play, but cut the margin to 62-49 with 55 seconds left on a 3-pointer by Cody Toppert and two 3-pointers by Will Scott. The Flyers finished with a 28-16 advantage on points in the paint and a 14-0 edge on fast break points. The game was originally scheduled for Saturday, but had to be postponed due to flooding in the area.
